author: jim
msg: The upside is, afaict, JUST for SVN. Any other PMC specific resource that could co-opt the commit privs ACL would need to recreate that data. Or even any other foundation wide resource (eg: http://people.apache.org/committer-index.html)

author: rhuijben
msg: In the local-local diff handling, only produce file changed reports if the
file has really changed. When using the builtin diff the result is the same
as the diff library won't find any changes.
(do_arbitrary_files_diff): Only tell that a file is modified if it
is modified. Not for every existing file.
